    ('HIST-B 315', 'EUROPEAN ANTI-SEMITISM FROM THE ENLIGHTENMENT TO THE HOLOCAUST', '32588', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 5:30 PM–6:45 PM', 'BH 307', 'Daniel Miehling', 6, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Examines the origins, character and development of anti-Semitism from the enlightenment to the post-Holocaust period. Asks whether anti-Semitism is a single phenomenon with a clear tradition and cause, or whether it has varied markedly over time and from country to country.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL (CASE) Culture Studies: Global Civ & Culture'], NULL),
    ('HIST-B 351', 'WESTERN EUROPE IN THE EARLY MIDDLE AGES', '29590', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'BH 203', 'Deborah Deliyannis', 4, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Evolution of European civilization from the fall of Rome, development of Christianity and Germanic invasions through Charlemagne''s Empire and the subsequent development of feudalism, manorialism, papacy, and Romanesque architecture.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL (CASE) Culture Studies: Global Civ & Culture'], NULL),
    ('HIST-B 362', 'EUROPE IN THE 20TH CENTURY II', '36964', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 3:00 PM–5:30 PM', 'SY 106', 'Julia Roos', 5, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'SYCAMORE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Economic, social, political, and military-diplomatic developments, 1900 to present. I. 1900-1930: origins, impact, and consequences of World War I; peacemaking; postwar problems; international communism and fascism; the Great Depression. II. 1930-present; depression politics; crisis of democracy; German National Socialism. World War II; cold war; postwar reconstruction and recovery.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('HIST-C 215', 'SPARTA AT WAR', '37481', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 6:40 PM–9:10 PM', 'BH 133', 'Eric Robinson', 1, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Introduction to the history of Sparta--the key events, institutions, leaders, and sources--while focusing on three broad questions: how did the Spartans create their unique society? What costs did their system exact from its people? How has Sparta been seen in contemporary culture?', ARRAY['IUB GenEd S&H credit
IUB GenEd World Culture credit
COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL (CASE) Culture Studies: Global Civ & Culture'], NULL),
    ('HIST-C 220', 'ANCIENT LEADERS AND LEADERSHIP', '29577', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 9:10 AM–10:00 AM', 'GA 0001', 'Colin Elliott', 2, 'Lecture', 'Lecture', '3', 'GLOBAL & INTERNATIONAL STUDIES', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'A close, critical and transdisciplinary study of leadership in ancient Greece and Rome--an investigation which intimately involves students in the lives of the leaders themselves as well as in the overriding cultural, political and social frameworks that defined these individuals as ''leaders'' in the first place.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd S&H credit
IUB GenEd World Culture credit
COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL (CASE) Culture Studies: Global Civ & Culture'], NULL),
