    ('HON-H 235', 'RELIGION IN LITERATURE, MUSIC, ART, AND PERFORMANCE', '30423', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 3:55 PM–5:10 PM', 'HU 111', 'Diane Reilly', 4, NULL, 'Seminar', '3', 'HUTTON HONORS COLLEGE', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Religion has been a theme in literature, music, and art for as long as there has been literature, music, and art. This course examines the origins, varieties, and meanings of religion and of sacred texts in poetry and prose, in music, in visual art and design, and in dramatic performances.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('HON-H 236', 'USE OF FORCE', '30426', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 9:35 AM–10:50 AM', 'HU 217', 'Edgar Illas', 1, NULL, 'Seminar', '3', 'HUTTON HONORS COLLEGE', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Considers coercion as a tool in the international arena, with particular attention to the use of military force. Analysis of case material from various time periods and geographical regions, as well as concepts from the social or behavioral sciences or from historical studies.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd S&H credit
COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('HON-H 237', 'LAW AND SOCIETY', '11262', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'LW 216', 'Gregory Canada', 0, NULL, 'Seminar', '3', 'LOWELL E. BAIER HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Law is not merely the normative framework creating order or fairness in public and private institutions. Among other things, it defines relationships among friends, creates predictability in city bus routes, and influences children''s moral character. This course considers law beyond the ordinary bounds of the courtroom and lawmaker''s chamber.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd S&H credit
COLL (CASE) S&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('HON-H 237', 'LAW AND SOCIETY', '12404', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'HU 217', 'Michael Weinman', 0, NULL, 'Seminar', '3', 'LOWELL E. BAIER HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Law is not merely the normative framework creating order or fairness in public and private institutions. Among other things, it defines relationships among friends, creates predictability in city bus routes, and influences children''s moral character. This course considers law beyond the ordinary bounds of the courtroom and lawmaker''s chamber.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd S&H credit
