    ('HUBI-B 400', 'COMPLEX PROBLEMS OF HUMANITY', '5404', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'BH 208', 'Thomas Siek', 13, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Capstone experience focusing on the interface of science and society. Students critically analyze real-world, contemporary challenges that impact the human condition. Topics vary based on faculty expertise and student interest. Emphasis is on student research or service learning, communication science, peer review, and making scientifically-informed arguments.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) N&M Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
